<DOC><DOCNO> AP881012-0015 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-12-88 0101EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Jobless-Entrepreneurs 1stLd-Writethru a0403 10-12 0108</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Jobless-Entrepreneurs, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0403,120</SECOND><HEAD>Three States to Try Turning Jobless Into Entrepreneurs</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: SUBS lede to delete extraneous words</NOTE><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three states _ Oregon, Massachusetts andMinnesota _ will test giving some laid off workers theirunemployment compensation benefits in lump sums for use in startingtheir own businesses.   The Labor Department said the demonstration project authorizedby Congress last year will divert about $8 million in theunemployment insurance fund to helping between 1,000 2,000beneficiaries ``become successful entrepreneurs.''   The program would provide cash allowances equal to the amountlaid off workers would normally receive in weekly unemploymentinsurance benefits, the department said.</TEXT></DOC>